def get_sentence_word_count(text_list):
    sent_count = 0
    word_count = 0
    vocab = {}
    for text in text_list:
        sentences=sent_tokenize(str(text).lower())
        sent_count = sent_count + len(sentences)
        for sentence in sentences:
            words=word_tokenize(sentence)
            for word in words:
                if(word in vocab.keys()):
                    vocab[word] = vocab[word] +1
                else:
                    vocab[word] =1 
    word_count = len(vocab.keys())
    return sent_count,word_count

def clean_text(text ): 
    text = text.translate(str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation))
    text1 = ''.join([w for w in text if not w.isdigit()]) 
    REPLACE_BY_SPACE_RE = re.compile('[/(){}\[\]\|@,;]')
    #BAD_SYMBOLS_RE = re.compile('[^0-9a-z #+_]')
    
    text2 = text1.lower()
    text2 = REPLACE_BY_SPACE_RE.sub('', text2) # replace REPLACE_BY_SPACE_RE symbols by space in text
    #text2 = BAD_SYMBOLS_RE.sub('', text2)
    return text2

def lemmatize_text(text):
    wordlist=[]
    lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer() 
    sentences=sent_tokenize(text)
    
    intial_sentences= sentences[0:1]
    final_sentences = sentences[len(sentences)-2: len(sentences)-1]
    
    for sentence in intial_sentences:
        words=word_tokenize(sentence)
        for word in words:
            wordlist.append(lemmatizer.lemmatize(word))
    for sentence in final_sentences:
        words=word_tokenize(sentence)
        for word in words:
            wordlist.append(lemmatizer.lemmatize(word))       
    return ' '.join(wordlist)

from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler

# Create the scaler
scaler = MinMaxScaler()

# Fit and transform the training data
X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)

# Transform the test data using the same scaler
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)

# Create the Multinomial Nave Bayes model
nb_classifier = MultinomialNB()

# Train the model on the scaled training data
nb_classifier.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)

# Make predictions on the scaled test data
y_test_pred = nb_classifier.predict(X_test_scaled)

# Assuming category_list contains your class labels
labels = np.unique(y_test)

# Sort labels for consistent ordering
labels.sort()

# Assuming y_test_pred contains your predicted labels
cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_test_pred, labels=labels)

# Plot confusion matrix
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20, 20))
ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1)
sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, cmap="Greens", ax=ax, fmt='g')  # annot=True to annotate cells

# labels, title, and ticks
ax.set_xlabel('Predicted labels')
ax.set_ylabel('True labels')
ax.set_title('Confusion Matrix')
ax.xaxis.set_ticklabels(labels)
ax.yaxis.set_ticklabels(labels)
plt.setp(ax.get_yticklabels(), rotation=30, horizontalalignment='right')
plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=30, horizontalalignment='right')
plt.show()

# Display accuracy and classification report
print(f'Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_pred)}')
print(classification_report(y_test, y_test_pred, labels=labels))

# Initialize LabelEncoder

# Train the model using the scaled training data

import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, accuracy_score, classification_report
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
from keras.models import Sequential, Model
from keras.layers import Dense, Input, concatenate
from keras.optimizers import Adam
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load your data
X = data['transcription'].tolist()
y = data['medical_specialty']

# Use TfidfVectorizer to convert text data to a TF-IDF representation
vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()
X_tfidf = vectorizer.fit_transform(X)

# Split the data consistently
X_train_tfidf, X_val_tfidf, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(
    X_tfidf, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42
)

# Encode labels using LabelEncoder
label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
y_train_encoded = label_encoder.fit_transform(y_train)
y_val_encoded = label_encoder.transform(y_val)

# Convert sparse matrix to dense array
X_train_dense = X_train_tfidf.toarray()
X_val_dense = X_val_tfidf.toarray()

# Model 1: 1D CNN
model_cnn = Sequential()
model_cnn.add(Dense(50, input_shape=(X_train_dense.shape[1],), activation='relu'))
model_cnn.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))
model_cnn.add(Dense(32, activation='relu'))

# Model 2: LSTM
model_lstm = Sequential()
model_lstm.add(Dense(50, input_shape=(X_train_dense.shape[1],), activation='relu'))
model_lstm.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model_lstm.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))
model_lstm.add(Dense(32, activation='relu'))

# Model 3: GRU
model_gru = Sequential()
model_gru.add(Dense(50, input_shape=(X_train_dense.shape[1],), activation='relu'))
model_gru.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model_gru.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))

# Combine models using Functional API
input_layer = Input(shape=(X_train_dense.shape[1],))
output_cnn = model_cnn(input_layer)
output_lstm = model_lstm(input_layer)
output_gru = model_gru(input_layer)

merged = concatenate([output_cnn, output_lstm, output_gru])
final_output = Dense(len(np.unique(y)), activation='softmax')(merged)

ensemble_model = Model(inputs=[input_layer], outputs=[final_output])

# Compile the model
ensemble_model.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.001), loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the ensemble model
ensemble_model.fit(X_train_dense, y_train_encoded, epochs=10, batch_size=64, validation_data=(X_val_dense, y_val_encoded))

# Make predictions on the validation set
y_val_pred = np.argmax(ensemble_model.predict(X_val_dense), axis=1)

# Print confusion matrix
cm = confusion_matrix(y_val_encoded, y_val_pred)
# Plot heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=label_encoder.classes_, yticklabels=label_encoder.classes_)
plt.xlabel('Predicted')
plt.ylabel('Actual')
plt.title('Confusion Matrix Heatmap')
plt.show()

# Print accuracy
accuracy = accuracy_score(y_val_encoded, y_val_pred)
print(f'\nAccuracy: {accuracy}')

# Print classification report
report = classification_report(y_val_encoded, y_val_pred)
print("\nClassification Report:")
print(report)

import numpy as np
import tensorflow as tf
from keras.models import Sequential, Model
from keras.layers import Dense, Input, concatenate
from keras.optimizers import Adam
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, accuracy_score, classification_report

# Encode labels using LabelEncoder
label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
y_train_encoded = label_encoder.fit_transform(y_train)
y_val_encoded = label_encoder.transform(y_val)

# Split the data
X_train_split, X_val_split, y_train_split, y_val_split = train_test_split(
    X_train_bow, y_train_encoded, test_size=0.2, random_state=42
)

# Model 1: 1D CNN
model_cnn = Sequential()
model_cnn.add(Dense(50, input_shape=(X_train_bow.shape[1],), activation='relu'))
model_cnn.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))
model_cnn.add(Dense(32, activation='relu'))

# Model 2: LSTM
model_lstm = Sequential()
model_lstm.add(Dense(50, input_shape=(X_train_bow.shape[1],), activation='relu'))
model_lstm.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model_lstm.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))
model_lstm.add(Dense(32, activation='relu'))

# Model 3: GRU
model_gru = Sequential()
model_gru.add(Dense(50, input_shape=(X_train_bow.shape[1],), activation='relu'))
model_gru.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model_gru.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))

# Combine models using Functional API
input_layer = Input(shape=(X_train_bow.shape[1],))
output_cnn = model_cnn(input_layer)
output_lstm = model_lstm(input_layer)
output_gru = model_gru(input_layer)

merged = concatenate([output_cnn, output_lstm, output_gru])
final_output = Dense(len(np.unique(y_train)), activation='softmax')(merged)

ensemble_model = Model(inputs=[input_layer], outputs=[final_output])

# Compile the model
ensemble_model.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.001), loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Convert sparse matrix to dense array
X_train_dense = X_train_split.toarray()

# Train the ensemble model
ensemble_model.fit(X_train_dense, y_train_split, epochs=10, batch_size=64, validation_data=(X_val_split.toarray(), y_val_split))

# Make predictions on the validation set
X_val_dense = X_val_bow.toarray()
y_val_pred = np.argmax(ensemble_model.predict(X_val_dense), axis=1)

# Print confusion matrix
cm = confusion_matrix(y_val_encoded, y_val_pred)
print("Confusion Matrix:")
print(cm)

# Print accuracy
accuracy = accuracy_score(y_val_encoded, y_val_pred)
print(f'\nAccuracy: {accuracy}')

# Print classification report
report = classification_report(y_val_encoded, y_val_pred)
print("\nClassification Report:")
print(report)

import numpy as np
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.models import Model
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Input, Embedding, Conv1D, LSTM, GRU, Concatenate, Dense, GlobalMaxPooling1D, GlobalAveragePooling1D
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, accuracy_score, classification_report
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.utils.class_weight import compute_class_weight

X = output_df.drop(['Text', 'Start', 'End', 'Entity Type'], axis=1)
y = output_df['Entity Type']

# Label encode the target variable
label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
y_encoded = label_encoder.fit_transform(y)

# Split the data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y_encoded, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Reshape the input data to include a sequence dimension
X_train_reshaped = X_train.values.reshape((X_train.shape[0], X_train.shape[1], 1))
X_test_reshaped = X_test.values.reshape((X_test.shape[0], X_test.shape[1], 1))

# Calculate class weights
class_weights = compute_class_weight('balanced', classes=np.unique(y_train), y=y_train)

# Convert class weights to a dictionary
class_weight_dict = {class_idx: weight for class_idx, weight in enumerate(class_weights)}

# Define the input layer
input_layer = Input(shape=(X_train_reshaped.shape[1], X_train_reshaped.shape[2]))

# 1D Convolutional Layer
conv1d_layer = Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=3, activation='relu')(input_layer)

# LSTM Layer
lstm_layer = LSTM(units=64, return_sequences=True)(conv1d_layer)

# GRU Layer
gru_layer = GRU(units=64, return_sequences=True)(conv1d_layer)

# Concatenate the output of LSTM and GRU layers
concatenated_layer = Concatenate()([lstm_layer, gru_layer])

# Global pooling layers
max_pooling_layer = GlobalMaxPooling1D()(concatenated_layer)
avg_pooling_layer = GlobalAveragePooling1D()(concatenated_layer)

# Concatenate the output of pooling layers
pooled_layer = Concatenate()([max_pooling_layer, avg_pooling_layer])

# Dense layers for final classification
dense_layer = Dense(64, activation='relu')(pooled_layer)
output_layer = Dense(len(np.unique(y_encoded)), activation='softmax')(dense_layer)

# Build the model
model = Model(inputs=input_layer, outputs=output_layer)

# Compile the model with class weights
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Display the model summary
model.summary()

# Train the model with class weights
history = model.fit(X_train_reshaped, y_train, epochs=10, batch_size=32, validation_split=0.1, class_weight=class_weight_dict)

# Evaluate the model on the test set
y_pred_nn = model.predict(X_test_reshaped)
y_pred_classes_nn = np.argmax(y_pred_nn, axis=1)

# Print confusion matrix
cm_nn = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_classes_nn)
print('Confusion Matrix:')
print(cm_nn)

# Plot confusion matrix as heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(cm_nn, annot=True, cmap="Blues", fmt='g', xticklabels=label_encoder.classes_, yticklabels=label_encoder.classes_)
plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
plt.ylabel('True labels')
plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Neural Network Model')
plt.show()

# Print accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score
accuracy_nn = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_classes_nn)
classification_rep_nn = classification_report(y_test, y_pred_classes_nn, target_names=label_encoder.classes_)

print(f'Accuracy: {accuracy_nn}')
print("Classification Report:\n", classification_rep_nn)

X_text = output_df['Text']
y = output_df['Entity Type']

# Label encode the target variable

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, accuracy_score, classification_report
from keras.models import Model
from keras.layers import Input, Embedding, Conv1D, LSTM, GRU, Dense, concatenate, Flatten
from keras.optimizers import Adam
from keras.preprocessing import sequence
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.sequence import pad_sequences
from sklearn.utils.class_weight import compute_class_weight

X_text = output_df['Text']
y = output_df['Entity Type']

# Label encode the target variable
label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
y_encoded = label_encoder.fit_transform(y)

# Use CountVectorizer instead of Tokenizer
max_features = 250  # You can adjust max_features based on your data
count_vectorizer = CountVectorizer(max_features=max_features)
X_text_counts = count_vectorizer.fit_transform(X_text)

# Convert the CountVectorizer output to a dense array
X_text_dense = X_text_counts.toarray()

# Pad sequences to a maximum length
max_len = 5
X_text_padded = pad_sequences(X_text_dense, maxlen=max_len)

# Split the data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_text_padded, y_encoded, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Define 1D CNN model
input_layer_cnn = Input(shape=(X_train.shape[1],), name='input_17')
embedding_layer_cnn = Embedding(input_dim=max_features + 1, output_dim=100)(input_layer_cnn)
cnn_layer = Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=3, activation='relu')(embedding_layer_cnn)
cnn_output = Dense(64, activation='relu')(cnn_layer)

cnn_model = Model(inputs=input_layer_cnn, outputs=cnn_output)

# Define LSTM model
input_layer_lstm = Input(shape=(X_train.shape[1],), name='input_18')
embedding_layer_lstm = Embedding(input_dim=max_features + 1, output_dim=100)(input_layer_lstm)
lstm_layer = LSTM(units=64, return_sequences=True)(embedding_layer_lstm)
lstm_output = Dense(64, activation='relu')(lstm_layer)

lstm_model = Model(inputs=input_layer_lstm, outputs=lstm_output)

# Define GRU model
input_layer_gru = Input(shape=(X_train.shape[1],), name='input_19')
embedding_layer_gru = Embedding(input_dim=max_features + 1, output_dim=100)(input_layer_gru)
gru_layer = GRU(units=64, return_sequences=True)(embedding_layer_gru)
gru_output = Dense(64, activation='relu')(gru_layer)

gru_model = Model(inputs=input_layer_gru, outputs=gru_output)

# Flatten the outputs of all models before concatenation
cnn_output = Flatten()(cnn_output)
lstm_output = Flatten()(lstm_output)
gru_output = Flatten()(gru_output)

# Concatenate outputs of all models
merged_layer = concatenate([cnn_output, lstm_output, gru_output])
ensemble_output = Dense(64, activation='relu')(merged_layer)
output_layer = Dense(len(label_encoder.classes_), activation='softmax')(ensemble_output)

# Create the ensemble model
ensemble_model = Model(inputs=[input_layer_cnn, input_layer_lstm, input_layer_gru], outputs=output_layer)

# Compile the model
ensemble_model.compile(optimizer=Adam(), loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Calculate class weights
class_weights = compute_class_weight('balanced', classes=np.unique(y_train), y=y_train)

# Convert class weights to a dictionary
class_weight_dict = {class_idx: weight for class_idx, weight in enumerate(class_weights)}

# Use the computed class weights during model training
ensemble_model.fit(
    {'input_17': X_train, 'input_18': X_train, 'input_19': X_train},
    y_train,
    epochs=15,
    batch_size=32,
    validation_split=0.2,
    class_weight=class_weight_dict
)

# Make predictions on the test set
y_pred_ensemble = np.argmax(ensemble_model.predict({'input_17': X_test, 'input_18': X_test, 'input_19': X_test}), axis=1)

# Print confusion matrix
cm_ensemble = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_ensemble)

# Create a heatmap of the confusion matrix for the ensemble model
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(cm_ensemble, annot=True, cmap="Blues", fmt='g', xticklabels=label_encoder.classes_, yticklabels=label_encoder.classes_)
plt.xlabel('Predicted labels')
plt.ylabel('True labels')
plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Ensemble Model')
plt.show()

# Print accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score
accuracy_ensemble = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_ensemble)
classification_rep_ensemble = classification_report(y_test, y_pred_ensemble, target_names=label_encoder.classes_)

print(f'Accuracy: {accuracy_ensemble}')
print("Classification Report:\n", classification_rep_ensemble)
